The paper deals with machine learning systems and proposes a lifelong learning framework that aims to reuse information from previously learned related tasks to learn future tasks in a feature-efficient manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
